title: The Cuff Links - Tracy (320)
description:
The Cuff Links - Tracy (320)

The Cuff Links was a late 60s bubblegum rock group similar to The Banana Splits, The 1910 Fruit Gum Company, Ohio Express, etc.  Lead by singer Ron Dante, The Cuff Links were a second version of The Archies who achieved Saturday morning cartoon fame in 1969 with their hit, "Sugar Sugar".  The Cuff Links never matched The Archies for popularity but they managed a modest hit with "Tracy" in 1969.
